The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Fit to play vs SA, says Sachin
                                                   Fit to play vs SA, says Sachin
            A STAFF REPORTER AMP; AGENCIES                      
	Calcutta: Sachin Tendulkar on Saturday dispelled concerns on his availability for the Test series against South Africa because of fitness problems.         
	Reacting to a report in an English daily, Sachin said in Mumbai: I have played the last match. As far as I am concerned I am fit. I have not said anything before on this. I will certainly play against South Africa. There is no doubt.         
	When contacted Board secretary Niranjan Shah said he had no idea about a fitness assessment report by physio John Gloster.         
	What report? I am not aware of any report submitted by Gloster, Shah said.         
	Sachin has been carrying an injury in the right hip region.         
	Sachin was named captain of the Mumbai Indians team for the forthcoming Indian Premier League to be held from April 18 and also unveiled the logo of the team at a promotional.         
	The first Test against South Africa commences in Chennai on March 26.                                                                                                                       
